
{{gstr|1492}} 
*εἴδω / eidō / i'-do

=== Etymology ===

A primary verb; used only in certain past tenses, the others being borrowed from the equivalent, [[ὀπτάνομαι]] {{GG|3700}} and [[ὁράω]] {{GG|3708}}; 
=== Verb ===
properly to [[see]] (literally or figuratively); by implication (in the perfect only) to [[know]]: - be aware, [[behold]], X can (+ not tell), [[consider]], (have) known (-ledge), [[look]] (on), [[perceive]], see, be sure, [[tell]], [[understand]], wist, wot. Compare [[ὀπτάνομαι]] {{GG|3700}}.